--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   booo! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  ~ ) anyway who should I take to get a wc? 1 group 2 groups full blown raid party? I got lots of higher level friends (like 62 days /played I level slow an my friends passed me up) should I just grab a group of 55  or what levels should I take I know I'll prolly need to level up a bit before I can hit it but all I really gotta worry about is getting through 54 and I should have no probs getting a group (my friends mostly group in places where they'll take a defensive tank over me any day. tho once I get defensive I can go too) any advice would be helpful thanks <p><HTML><BODY><a Target="_top" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47996" ><img src="http://ezb.flamingtext.com/ezb/01/12/03/flamingtext_com.053510637.gif" border=0 alt="Click for magelo profile"></a></BODY></HTML></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukristoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kristoc</A> at: 2/10/02 2:49:44 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/uraaj.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raaj</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Seasoned Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 300<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/10/02 10:42:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=528.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://raaj.freewebspace.com/sigs/personalpic.gif width=104 height=143></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: obtaining a wavecrasher</span><hr size=1> One thing you also have to look at is teaching that monk agro control =P<br><br>Keeping agro on the main tank isnt always the main tanks job. Everyone else should watch their own agro.<br><br>It's not a sin to turn off attack for a few rounds. <p>[60 Warlord] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=8921">Raaj</a> <<a href="http://www.clantaveren.com">Clan Ta Veren</a>></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udaramineq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DaraminEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 15<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/10/02 5:35:50 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=528.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: obtaining a wavecrasher</span><hr size=1> Two additional pieces of advice (agro control being the first -- very true -- piece).<br><br>1) Haste -- if you can get better haste, your agro will go higher than someone who doesn't have it.<br><br>2) Chanter agro buffs -- I can't emphasize enough how big a difference these make.<br><br>Wavecrasher has been discussed enough here that you should be able to get one. But let me tell you, my guild has two active 60 warriors, me and another guy. I have a CoF, he has an RBB, I have a CBoL and a Jade Mace, he has a CBoL and a Wavecrasher. We trade MA duties off, and yesterday were in Sky on the 5th island. I was botting a cleric, so he was MA for that, but I was getting a lot of the DT's he wanted, with me not taunting at all and sometimes not even 100% on the mob because it would move while I was healing someone. I think the main factor there was haste. I would have switched to lower delay weapons but one of us needed to get the DT and it didn't really matter which of us it was, it's just that the Wavecrasher wasn't keeping him as high on the list in a lot of cases. That was with Avatar, so presumably he was at max dex.<br><br>Daramin Anklebiter<br>Warlord of Xev<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukristoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kristoc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/10/02 6:59:40 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=528.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: obtaining a wavecrasher</span><hr size=1> as for the aggro control it wasn't too great i'm a ta which means that if there is a 2 pull the ma and sa each take one. and if one of them dies then i step up and take aggro this is hard, i don't get the advantage of soloing the mob for a bit i am supposed to just take aggro. i know in most situations i could be the 4th or 5th person on the mobs aggro list 1being ma 2 being other uber dmg dealer 3ma's cleric then maybe me then maybe another dmg dealer. but on 3 pulls i'm fine (ma grabs one sa grabs one i grab the weakest one) i get that whole soloing thing the entire time the raid party is killin the ma mob and the sa mob and fourtunatly i have a damn good cleric behind me keepin me alive and i can tank that mob till it's dead if the ma disn't get aggro beforehand (he can taunt i just have to taunt with dmg and proc) there was a sg raid today we killed the spirit about 3 times no wc dropped and i'd likely not get it if it did unless the ma or sa didn't want it. looks like this is something i'm gonna have to do in like 2 high lvl groups. yeah haste matters a ton. been on 5 naggy raids and never seen a cof drop tho. dosn't look like there will be many more naggy raids since rage spawns in sf now,oh well i i can just kill ixablat or something. but even with the haste i'll still need a faster weapon than lsoee don't get me wrong in any position other than an assist position i'll use my lsoee in a heartbeat just such a great ratio great weapon for general damage output but not fast enuf for ma stuff. what lvl does the chanter get aggro buffs? are these drop only? and where can i get some for my chanter? <p><HTML><BODY><a Target="_top" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47996" ><img src="http://ezb.flamingtext.com/ezb/01/12/03/flamingtext_com.053510637.gif" border=0 alt="Click for magelo profile"></a></BODY></HTML></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/udaramineq.showPublicProfile?language=EN>DaraminEQ</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 17<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/10/02 10:34:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=528.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: obtaining a wavecrasher</span><hr size=1> Any monk has no excuse for keeping agro unless they want it. They can dump it at almost any point just by feigning. If you're worried about a cleric being higher, then a monk probably _shouldn't_ dump the agro just then. But normally a cleric will be around the middle of the list in most circumstances. I get summoned on my cleric mostly when I either 1) CH the puller immediately after they make it back to camp -- usually means I'm immediately in DB... 2) Healing a number of people with Divine Light... Generally that's it.<br><br>There are two versions of the chanter agro buff -- 10% and 30%. The 30% ones are mid 50's, drop in ssra and other places that drop the upper-level spells (ssra, akheva, i'm sure more like grieg's etc -- not fungus). The lower ones are storebought and are mid 30's spells if I remember correctly. Even the 10% ones do a lot, if you're close, they will bump you to the top of the list every time. They were make or break for me in HoT before I hit 60.<br><br>Daramin Anklebiter<br>Warlord of Xev<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukristoc.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kristoc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 3:18:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=528.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: obtaining a wavecrasher</span><hr size=1> sweet we'll have to get a copy of that spell at least the 10% version tho we have 3 chanters 55+ so we'll prolly go for the higher one if somone dosn't have it in their bank or something (usually what happens to important spells) <p><HTML><BODY><a Target="_top" href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=47996" ><img src="http://ezb.flamingtext.com/ezb/01/12/03/flamingtext_com.053510637.gif" border=0 alt="Click for magelo profile"></a></BODY></HTML></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/usandrakspiritwalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sandrak Spiritwalker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/11/02 1:46:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=528.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: obtaining a wavecrasher</span><hr size=1> Wavecrasher is a decent taunt and not real hard to get.  Just kill the elementals in SG down near Elna Kelpweaver and you will get one without much effort at all unless something changed from when I was there.  We got 3 in a pretty short period of time. (couple days)<br><br>Willsapper is better.  I am sure its not the best, I am sure there are better taunt weapons.  However, when I want aggro, I have no problem getting it and holding it.<br><br> <p><table width="50%" border="0"><tr> <td width="62%" height="72"> <div align="center"><b><a href="http://home.austin.rr.com/mytoy/"><font color="#CC9900">Sandrak Spiritwalker</font></a></b></div></td></table></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ugorgirmgrudgebearer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gorgirm Grudgebearer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/14/02 4:37:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebattlefield.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=528.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/p_sword.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: obtaining a wavecrasher</span><hr size=1> another weapon i have surprisingly found for argo is the Chekali whip from DN off the Chekali them selfs (sorry im a dorf i cant spell). 9/19 with the proc of Strong Disease which argo greatly and when paired with my Frostbringer i can hold argo fairly well. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=91906>Gorgirm Grudgebearer</a><BR> Dwarven Warlord of The Kindred<BR>Master Drunk<BR><BR><a href=http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=80021>Canable Tafa'Ched</a><BR>Iks